===Etymology===
Old Engish ''[[ancor]]'', from Latin ''[[ancora]]'', from (or cognate with) {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἄγκῡρα]]}}'''.  The modern spelling is a sixteenth-century modification to better represent the Latin misspelling ''anchora''.

